From: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
Subject: [PATCH] os/memstore: declare memstore as STATIC

v21 split the monolithic libos into an `os` static library plus
per-backend sublibraries linked back into it.  `os` STATIC takes
`PRIVATE memstore` (src/os/CMakeLists.txt) while `memstore` itself
takes `PRIVATE os` (src/os/memstore/CMakeLists.txt), forming a cycle.

CMake allows such cycles only between STATIC libraries.  Upstream
builds leave BUILD_SHARED_LIBS undefined (CMake default OFF) so
memstore ends up STATIC and the cycle is accepted.

openRuyi's %cmake macro presets BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON, which turns
memstore into a SHARED library and trips the cmake error:

  CMake Error: The inter-target dependency graph contains the following
  strongly connected component (cycle):
    "os" of type STATIC_LIBRARY
      depends on "memstore" (weak)
    "memstore" of type SHARED_LIBRARY
      depends on "os" (weak)
  At least one of these targets is not a STATIC_LIBRARY.

Declare memstore as STATIC unconditionally so the type matches `os`
regardless of BUILD_SHARED_LIBS.  bluestore (the sibling backend) is
already OBJECT and is unaffected.

STATIC (not OBJECT) is required here: CMake allows dependency cycles
only among STATIC libraries, so an OBJECT memstore trips the exact same
"At least one of these targets is not a STATIC_LIBRARY" error as a
SHARED one (verified with a minimal repro).  The bluestore comparison is
not a counter-example: bluestore is OBJECT but does not link `os`, so it
is not part of any cycle.  memstore's cycle comes from its own
`target_link_libraries(memstore PRIVATE os)`.

Not proposed upstream: upstream builds with BUILD_SHARED_LIBS unset
(default OFF) and does not support/test the ON build, so this is
downstream config tuning.  The clean upstream fix would be to break the
cycle at its source -- drop memstore's link dependency on `os` (mirroring
bluestore, which gets by without it) rather than change the library type
-- but that needs verifying memstore still builds without linking `os`,
which is out of scope here.
---
 src/os/memstore/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/os/memstore/CMakeLists.txt b/src/os/memstore/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/src/os/memstore/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/os/memstore/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 include(CheckCXXCompilerFlag)

-add_library(memstore
+add_library(memstore STATIC
   MemStore.cc)
 target_link_libraries(memstore PRIVATE os)
 check_cxx_compiler_flag("-Wno-maybe-uninitialized"
